      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520$a">
         <head>Scope and Content
</head>
         <p>
The papers of the University History Officer, Charles E. Moran, contain general correspondence as well as topical files concerning the reprinting of Anna Barringer's memoirs; Virginius Dabney's history of the University of Virginia; Founder's Day; the inauguration of Frank L. Hereford; the Indian Massacre of 1622; a portrait of James Rogers McConnell; the Shannon Garden; Southampton County, Va.; University of Virginia history including a 1971 article on Jesse Beams, a copy of Eleanor Lile Tucker's memoirs, 1968, a copy of B. F. D. Runk's speech <title render="doublequote">My friends,</title> and a poem by Ray Bice honoring Senator Edward Stone; and the Virginia History and Museums Federation.
</p>
         <p>
General correspondence includes information on Mrs. Lindsay Hay's copy of her father's <title render="doublequote">Honor Men</title> and the University of Virginia's housing Library of Congress documents during World War II. 
</p>
      </scopecontent>
